  "prompt": "Which is the best recommended book for CA-CPT?",
  "response": "As of my last update, the CA-CPT (Chartered Accountancy Common Proficiency Test) has been replaced by the CA Foundation course. However, if you're preparing for examinations in the CA stream, some well-recommended books for foundational concepts include:\n\n1. **\"Foundation Course\" by Dinesh Madan** - A comprehensive resource that covers various topics in accounting, business laws, and economics.\n\n2. **\"Accounting for CA Foundation\" by Anil Kumar** - Focuses on the fundamentals of accounting with clear explanations.\n\n3. **\"Business Laws\" by S. P. Jain** - A good reference for understanding the legal framework relevant to commerce and business.\n\n4. **\"Fundamentals of Economics\" by R. G. Gupta** - Offers insights into basic economic principles valuable for CA aspirants.\n\n5. **\"CA Foundation\" Study Materials from ICAI** - The Institute of Chartered Accountants of India provides study materials that are specifically tailored to the syllabus.\n\nAlways ensure to check the latest syllabus and guidelines from ICAI, as they can change, and the best resources may vary over time. Additionally, joining coaching classes or online courses can also provide structured preparation guidance.",
